line_1: Who seem'd as one from mortals long estrang'd,
line_2: His lost address and comely visage chang'd:

line_1: Their hopes, desires and purposes estranged
line_2: From things terrestrial, and divinely changed,

line_1: There center all my woes, thy heart estrang'd,
line_2: I weep my lover, not my fortune, chang'd;

line_1: Still thy cold look was scornful, and estranged,
line_2: Sad, though I wept the friend, the lover chang'd,

line_1: Their virtues hid, their friends estranged;
